mentor-widget-image\" data-id=\"7c42854\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" width=\"784\" height=\"525\" src=\"https:\/\/gcsinternational.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/UN-with-peace-bell-and-dove1-e1497200204720.jpg\" class=\"attachment-large size-large\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https:\/\/gcsinternational.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/UN-with-peace-bell-and-dove1-e1497200204720.jpg 784w, https:\/\/gcsinternational.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/UN-with-peace-bell-and-dove1-e1497200204720-300x201.jpg 300w, https:\/\/gcsinternational.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/UN-with-peace-bell-and-dove1-e1497200204720-768x514.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 784px) 100vw, 784px\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-3af6a50 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"3af6a50\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-db311f6\" data-id=\"db311f6\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-1f9196e elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"1f9196e\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">WHAT IS THE INTERNATIONAL DAY OF PEACE?<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-297cb90 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"297cb90\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-ba9bf3f\" data-id=\"ba9bf3f\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-16acc2e elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"16acc2e\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><strong>The International Day of Peace (&#8220;Peace Day&#8221;) is observed around the world each year on 21 September. Established in 1981 by unanimous United Nations resolution, Peace Day provides a globally shared date for all humanity to commit to Peace above all differences and to contribute to building a Culture of Peace.This is a long established universal website which serves all involved in Peace Day, beginning annually with the 100-day Countdown.This year is particularly significant: It is the 20th Anniversary of the UN Resolution on the Programmer of Action on a Culture of Peace.<\/strong><strong>Let us all create Peace Day everyday! UN Secretary General, Antonio Guterres, delivers his 100-day countdown to the International Day of Peace message.<\/strong><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-c66a9cc elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"c66a9cc\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-c64f168\" data-id=\"c64f168\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-9238eb9 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"9238eb9\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"peaceGraphic\"><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.un.org\/en\/events\/peaceday\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/internationaldayofpeace.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/2021-IDP-graphic.jpg\" \/><\/a><\/strong><\/div><div><p><strong>2021 Peace Day Theme:<br \/>Recovering Better for an Equitable and Sustainable World<\/strong><br \/><strong>We invite you to join the efforts of the United Nations family as we focus on recovering better for a more equitable and peaceful world.<\/strong><\/p><\/div>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-9a11b52\" data-id=\"9a11b52\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-eb48d91 elementor-widget elementor-widget-image\" data-id=\"eb48d91\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" width=\"604\" height=\"403\" src=\"https:\/\/gcsinternational.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/Children-with-U.N.-Flags1.jpg\" class=\"attachment-large size-large\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https:\/\/gcsinternational.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/Children-with-U.N.-Flags1.jpg 604w, https:\/\/gcsinternational.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/Children-with-U.N.-Flags1-300x200.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 604px) 100vw, 604px\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-b18e04d elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"b18e04d\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><strong>From education to the arts, social justice to sports, health to the environment, neighborhood issues to service for others, there are many ways to participate in Peace Day! We invite you to create a public or private activity related to peace, spread the word about Peace Day and\/or attend an event in your community. <a href=\"https:\/\/gcsinternational.in\/u-n-international-day-of-peace-21-september\/\">Learn more<\/a><br \/><\/strong><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>GLOBAL COMMON SOCIETY INTERNATIONAL (INDIA) International Day of Peace WHAT IS THE INTERNATIONAL DAY OF PEACE? The International Day of Peace (&#8220;Peace Day&#8221;) is observed around the world each year on 21 September. Established in 1981 by unanimous United Nations resolution, Peace Day provides a globally shared date for all humanity to commit to Peace &hellip;<\/p>\n<p class=\"read-more\"> <a class=\"\" href=\"https:\/\/gcsinternational.in\/international-day-of-peace\/\"> <span class=\"screen-reader-text\">International Day of Peace<\/span> Read More &raquo;<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","met